May 26 2017 - Products
Inframe Engine Kit Designed for Navistar DT466 EGR
Reliance Power Parts
Reliance Power Parts’ inframe engine kits and service components are designed for the Navistar DT466 EGR engines used in medium-duty trucks.
Tags: Preventive Maintenance, Diesel Engines, Navistar, EGR



April 14 2016 - Equipment
Navistar Shows HX520, the Series' 4th Version
International Truck
Navistar unveiled the fourth version of its severe-duty International HX series, the HX520, with a forward-set steer axle, a 120-inch bumper-to-back-of-cab measurement and Cummins' ISX15 diesel. The new model will serve the heavy haul tractor, construction dump and platform stake/crane markets, the manufacturer said.
Tags: International, Navistar, Equipment, Vocational Trucks, Severe Duty



October 5 2014 - Products
Navistar Enhances OnCommand Connection
Navistar
SAN DIEGO – Navistar announced several new OnCommand Connection remote diagnostics features at the American Trucking Associations Management Conference and Exhibition.
Tags: Telematics, Information Technology, Navistar, Diagnostics, ATA MC&E


June 26 2014 - Products
Rand McNally Devices Integrate with Navistar’s Diagnostic System
Rand McNally
Diagnostic fault code data collected from Rand McNally in-cab fleet management devices now integrates with Navistar’s OnCommand Connection remote diagnostics system, the company announced June 26.
Tags: Rand McNally, Navistar, Information Technology


March 10 2014 - Products
Navistar Adds Capabilities to OnCommand Diagnostics/Telematics Platform
Nav
TMC, NASHVILLE – Navistar has integrated Mitchell 1 Repair-Connect.net and in-bay service tools from Nexiq Technologies and Noregon Systems into its OnCommand Connection remote diagnostics system.
Tags: Telematics, Information Technology, Navistar, Mitchell 1, Diagnostics, Nexiq, Noregon Systems


March 6 2014 - Products
Navistar Announces SCR for MaxxForce Midrange Engines, Plus TerraStar Enhancements
Navistar Inc.
Navistar announced enhancements to its severe service and medium-duty product lines, including adding selective catalytic reduction emissions technology to its higher-horsepower midrange engines.
Tags: Emissions, Navistar, Medium-Duty Trucks, SCR, TerraStar, Engines


March 4 2014 - Products
Navistar Announces Diamond Logic Electrical Feature Bundles 
Navistar, Diamond Logic
WORK TRUCK SHOW -- Navistar announced new Diamond Logic feature bundles specific to the vocational truck market. Feature bundles are categorized by usage and body integration such as dry van, dump and utility as well as outline features relevant to operations of the particular application.
Tags: Navistar, Diamond Logic, Work Truck Show, NTEA



January 21 2014 - Products
LED Head Lights Now Standard on International ProStar Trucks
Navistar
Navistar International Corp. announced that Truck-Lite high-visibility LED headlamps are now standard on International ProStar Class 8 on-highway trucks.
Tags: Navistar, Headlights, ProStar, LED Lighting



January 13 2014 - Products
Navistar Launches Truck Configurators For International ProStar, DuraStar, TerraStar
Navistar
Navistar International Corp. announced the availability of its new, re-designed online truck configurators for International ProStar, DuraStar,  and TerraStar models on Internationaltrucks.com. The configurators allow customers to virtually design, build and customize their International Truck’s cab, exterior, interior, powertrain and more.
Tags: Information Technology, Navistar



December 23 2013 - Products
 Navistar Releases First International DuraStar Vehicles To Market With Cummins ISB Engines
Navistar
Navistar Inc. announced that it has started customer shipments of its first International DuraStar vehicles with the Cummins ISB 6.7-liter engine. The first units were released from the company's Escobedo, Mexico assembly plant.
Tags: Cummins, Navistar, Engines, Medium-Duty Trucks



October 21 2013 - Products
Navistar Offers Portfolio of Fully Automated Transmissions Options
Navistar, Cummins, Eaton, Allison
Navistar Inc. announced it is the first to market with a portfolio of fully automatic and automated manual transmissions for a range of applications, according to the company. The options will be available on International ProStar and International TranStar vehicles. 
Tags: Cummins, Eaton, Navistar, Allison



October 20 2013 - Products
Navistar OnCommand Connection Remote Diagnostics System to Debut in 2014
Navistar
Navistar demonstrated its new OnCommand Connection remote diagnostics system at the American Trucking Associations Management Conference and Exhibition. Navistar says it's the first single remote diagnostics portal to use an open architecture system with fleets’ existing telematics providers. 
Tags: Telematics, Navistar, Diagnostics, ATA2013



October 17 2013 - Products
New Allison TC10 Tractor Transmission Available for Order at Navistar
Allison, Navistar
Allison Transmission Holdings Inc. announced that the new TC10 tractor transmission is now offered on Navistar's International ProStar and TranStar models with MaxxForce 13 engines with SCR. 
Tags: Navistar, Allison



October 17 2013 - Products
Navistar Offers Holland Fifth Wheels on International Trucks
Navistar, SAF-Holland
SAF-Holland announced that Holland standard duty fifth wheel models are now a published option on Navistar’s International Truck models and available for immediate on-line installation.
Tags: Navistar, Fifth Wheels, SAF-Holland



October 15 2013 - Products
Navistar offers Jost as Option on Internationals  
Navistar, Jost
Jost International fifth wheels will be available as factory installed options on International trucks manufactured by Navistar. Published Jost data book assemblies will include their cast iron, lightweight, cab actuated release and low lube product offerings.  
Tags: Navistar, Fifth Wheels, Jost International



October 8 2013 - Products
Omnitek Engineering Establishes Alliance With Reviva
Omnitek, Reviva
Omnitek Engineering Corp. has established a strategic alliance with Minnesota-based diesel engine remanufacturer Reviva to produce a "drop-in" natural gas engine for the Navister DT 466E and DT 530E heavy-duty truck engines, with plans to offer additional engine models. 
Tags: Natural Gas, Navistar, Remanufactured Parts, Omnitek



September 4 2013 - Products
Navistar to Add Cummins ISB to International Trucks; MaxxForce Diesels Continue 
Navistar, Cummins
Navistar International Corp. says it will offer the Cummins ISB 6.7-liter diesel in its International DuraStar medium-duty trucks and CE series IC school buses, but that this doesn't mean it's getting out of the engine business.
Tags: Cummins, Navistar, Medium-Duty Trucks, SCR, Light & Medium, Engines


August 8 2013 - Products
International Enhances Owner Loyalty Program
Navistar International Corp.
Navistar International Corp. announced enhanced benefits of International Advantage, the company’s owner loyalty program. Benefits now include advanced fleet management tools, 24/7 dedicated concierge service and exclusive offers on vehicles, parts, service and more. 
Tags: Navistar, International Trucks



August 8 2013 - Products
Navistar Begins Production Of International TranStar With 13-Liter SCR Engine
Navistar
Navistar Inc. announced the launch of its International TranStar regional haul tractor with MaxxForce 13 engine with Selective Catalytic Reduction emissions technology. The TranStar is the fifth heavy-duty International truck model to transition to SCR technology since December 2012.

Tags: Navistar, SCR, International TranStar


July 16 2013 - Products
Navistar Selects Dana Axles, Driveshafts for Newest Vehicle
Navistar
Dana Holding Corp. has been named the standard and exclusive supplier of steer axles, drive axles, and driveshafts on the new International TerraStar 4x4 medium-duty truck. Navistar recently began customer deliveries of the all-wheel-drive vehicles.
Tags: Navistar, Dana



July 16 2013 - Products
Navistar Launches Heavy-Duty International WorkStar With 13-Liter SCR Engine
Navistar
Navistar Inc. announced the launch of its heavy-duty International WorkStar vocational trucks powered by the company's 13-liter engine with Selective Catalytic Reduction emissions technology. The WorkStar is the fourth heavy-duty International truck model to transition to SCR technology since December 2012.
Tags: Navistar, WorkStar



May 28 2013 - Products
Navistar Now Shipping TerraStar 4x4
Navistar International
Navistar has started shipping its first International TerraStar 4x4 units. Launched in 2010, originally with a 4x2 configuration, this work truck offers more capabilities to customers, says the company, and positions International Truck to participate in a significant piece of the market where it didn’t previously have a presence.
Tags: Navistar, TerraStar



April 11 2013 - Products
International Launches Truck Portfolio with Cummins ISX15
Navistar, Cummins
Navistar International Corp. re-launched its International 9900i and PayStar 5900 SBA models at ExpoCam, Canada's National Truck Show. 
Tags: Cummins, International, Navistar, Engines, Emissions, SCR


March 21 2013 - Products
Eaton Develops Navistar-Specific Fuel-Saving UltraShift Plus Transmissions  
Eaton
Eaton launched a new family of UltraShift Plus transmissions designed exclusively for Navistar to maximize fuel efficiency in linehaul applications.
Tags: Cummins, Eaton, Navistar, Fuel Economy, Transmissions, Mid-America Trucking Show



